  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, depending how lucky you were and how much damage you did and how much did the front end of the train pull down the rest of the-- rest of the cars into the embankment really would, would, would really influence it.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course, there was a second rail line, and the question was, you know, would, would you also block the traffic on the second line?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the geometry was very important.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But Bat'ko was a very experienced man, and he was basically looking for places on a high embankment on a curve, not far from the edge of a forest, where you could come in and get out very quickly.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They had a topographic map, and they said, well, is this a good place, or that place?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I knew how to read topographic maps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I suggested where we would go, and we proceeded shortly thereafter to a location near a town called Opatova where we arrived in a drizzling rain, marching mostly not during full daylight, but mostly early in the morning and before it got really dark.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By that time, of course, the whole area was-- the mountains were subject to open fire.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, the Germans could shoot anybody they saw on site, so the, the, the big danger was, in fact, being detected by the peasants who saw us trooping by and who could inform on us.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we, by and large, travelled through, through, through the woods.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Usually, I was in the front because I know the area going over the trail.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I carried, initially, only two hand grenades, but I had a knapsack full of [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] explosives, which were five kilo boxes made out of light steel.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
